&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frimley Health NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department of Obstetrics and Gynaecology&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post CCT Clinical Fellow &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(1 year fixed term contract with potential for further extension)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Frimley Health NHS Foundation Trust is one of the largest acute trusts in the South East, comprising Frimley Park Hospital and Heatherwood and Wexham Park Hospitals. Frimley Park Hospital was rated as ‘Outstanding’ by the Care Quality Commission in 2014.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is designed for an individual who has recently obtained a CCT in Obstetrics and Gynaecology and wishes to develop their special/sub-specialist interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department can offer the post within Urogynaecology, Fetal Medicine, Oncology and Emergency/Ambulatory Gynaecology/EPU, depending on the special interest of the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There may be opportunity for clinical research in these areas. In addition the successful candidate will be expected to develop managerial skills and gain further experience in teaching, audit and clinical leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional duties would include resident daytime third on call weekends (1 in 7) and third on call night shifts supporting the Registrar on call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in partnership with the MoD we have an integrated military and civilian workforce. Working with 17 Consultants you will also be supported by a dedicated, dynamic and enthusiastic medical, nursing and midwifery team incorporating many extended roles covering audit, clinical risk, practice development and IT, so if you’re comfortable working as part of an innovative team, with an enthusiasm for obstetrics and gynaecology, then you will thrive in our lively fast paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like further information, please contact Miss Helen Walker, Consultant Obstetrician &amp; Gynaecologist, on helen.walker210@nhs.net or 01276 526079&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 11th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
